163
00:08:55,628 --> 00:09:03,233
So in his publication, in the commissioner's update that he puts out, he has identified state law as the basis

164
00:09:05,026 --> 00:09:11,690
for saying that participation in standardized testing is mandatory.

165
00:09:12,530 --> 00:09:19,174
The statute, he writes, does not contain an opt-out provision for parents to remove their children from participating.

166
00:09:19,715 --> 00:09:25,658
So he's citing Mass General Law's Chapter 69, Section 11 for that statement.

167
00:09:27,639 --> 00:09:33,883
And he references the landmark 1993 Massachusetts Education Reform Act as the basis.

168
00:09:35,970 --> 00:09:40,812
As you know and as I've mentioned, we have selected PARCC for 2016.

169
00:09:42,292 --> 00:09:52,595
So again, grades 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, and 8 are administering PARCC for English Language Arts, Arts and Mathematics, and Science for MCAS.

170
00:09:54,656 --> 00:09:55,776
So we had that option.

171
00:09:56,437 --> 00:10:00,198
We are held harmless for our participation in PARCC.

172
00:10:01,698 --> 00:10:08,344
So I'm going to go down to the next part of the report where, and I'm going to read this verbatim because it comes directly, again, from the commissioner.

173
00:10:09,443 --> 00:10:12,184
So in his guidance, he has written the following.

174
00:10:12,824 --> 00:10:20,445
In some instances, a student may refuse to take a test either of his or own volition or at the direction of a parent.

175
00:10:20,905 --> 00:10:33,888
In these cases, the Department of Ed, or I should say the Board of Education, asks principals to encourage parents to rethink their refusal and remind them that the assessments are a valuable gauge of their students' and schools' progress.

176
00:10:35,094 --> 00:10:39,640
We ask principals and test proctors to handle refusals with sensitivity.

177
00:10:40,581 --> 00:10:47,289
Students should not be pressured to take the test, nor should they be punished for not taking the test.

178
00:10:48,243 --> 00:11:00,790
They may sit quietly and read in the testing room, but if they are distracting others in the class who are taking the test, it would be appropriate for them to move to another location within the school with adult supervision.

179
00:11:01,571 --> 00:11:06,654
There is no requirement to provide formal or informal instruction to these students during the test period.

180
00:11:07,294 --> 00:11:13,418
Having them do work or read a book is sufficient, provided that the material is separate from the content being assessed on that day.

181
00:11:17,788 --> 00:11:26,794
So he issued this guidance in response to a number of inquiries about whether or not opting out of mandated state assessment was required.

182
00:11:29,756 --> 00:11:35,319
He then identifies why student participation in these tests is essential, as you can see in your report.

183
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:45,726
The results of these assessments provide valuable feedback to districts, to administrators, and to students and parents about

184
00:11:46,863 --> 00:11:50,574
about their achievement or lack thereof.

185
00:11:52,402 --> 00:12:00,848
They write, he writes, legislators and taxpayers expect an objective assessment of student and school performance in return for very significant investment of public funds.

186
00:12:01,729 --> 00:12:04,591
So in other words, the public wants to know how our students are doing.

187
00:12:06,252 --> 00:12:07,753
We are concerned about the following.

188
00:12:07,933 --> 00:12:16,339
A low participation rate on the statewide assessments can adversely affect a district's performance rating in the state and federal accountability system.

189
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:20,963
So we are concerned that if our accountability, excuse me, if our attendance

190
00:12:22,740 --> 00:12:26,163
participation rate is low, it could affect our accountability.

191
00:12:27,524 --> 00:12:30,006
We don't anticipate that the high school will be a problem.

192
00:12:30,546 --> 00:12:41,415
They are taking MCAS, but in the event that a parent were to opt out of the MCAS test for a grade 10 student, they would have a very difficult time earning a competency determination.

193
00:12:44,298 --> 00:12:50,003
Towards the end of the report, I reiterate that concern or that effect on accountability.

194
00:12:51,895 --> 00:12:58,442
So it is important to keep in mind it is a mandated test backed up by law.

195
00:12:59,082 --> 00:13:08,572
